    "The introduction of Bitcoin has ignited substantial excitement within financial markets, and this phenomenon poses an existential risk to certain conventional financial functions (Härdle et al. 2020).",
    "Subsequently, new cryptocurrencies such as Ethereum, Ripple, and Litecoin and stable coins such as Tether have also been introduced, potentially serving as competitors or alternatives to Bitcoin.",
